net.novazero.lib.ikbus

Class UnknownIKBusMessageCatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.novazero.lib.ikbus.UnknownIKBusMessageCatcher
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IKBusMessageParser

    public class UnknownIKBusMessageCatcher
extends Object
implements IKBusMessageParser
    I/K-bus message parser that serves as a fall-back in case its delegate parser is unable to parse a message. This message parser will ensure that the parseMessage method never returns null.. In case the delegate parser is unable to parse a message, this class will wrap the packet in an instance of UnknownIKBusMessage.
    Author:
    Daan Scheerens

      • parseMessage

        public IKBusMessage parseMessage(IKBusPacket packet)
                          throws IKBusMessageParseException
        Parses I/K-bus message that is contained in the specified packet using the delegate parser. If this parser is unable to parse the message, then this method will wrap the packet in an UnknownIKBusMessage instance, thereby ensuring the result of this function is never null.
        Specified by:
        parseMessage in interface IKBusMessageParser
        Parameters:
        packet - The packet containing the I/K-bus message that is to be parsed.
        Returns:
        The message that was parsed from the given packet.
        Throws:
        IKBusMessageParseException - If an error occurs while the delegate parser is trying to parse a recognized packet.
